description: Cambridge suffer a first defeat since Neil Harris returned as head coach as they lose 1-0 at home to Stevenage.
title: Cambridge United 0-1 Stevenage
maintext:
Cambridge Unitedâ€™s 2-0 win in October ended their five-game losing run against Stevenage in the league.
After winning none of their first five Football League visits to Cambridge from 2015 to 2019 (D2 L3), Stevenage have since won each of their last three.
Cambridge United are looking to win back-to-back home league games for just the second time this season (after doing so in October) having won their last such game 2-0 over Stockport.
